commentary: Nasir Hossain to Rossouw, OUT Nasir gets RR first ball. He has missed a straight ball. Hurries on with the arm on off, RR camps back in the crease and wants to slap it through the covers after stepping away a touch but does not connect. commentary: Mahmudullah to Miller, OUT Mashrafe claims the catch. Miller walks off. South Africa slide further. Miller steps out,  Mahmudullah is aware of it as he fires it flat on the pads. commentary: Mahmudullah to du Plessis, no run Mahmudullah belts out an appeal for lbw. Not given. Looks tight. Mahmadullah is keen on a review. Mashrafe goes for it. Turns in and fizzes from outside off, beats the inside edge and strikes him in line with off/ just a shade outside off on the knee-roll of the back pad. Mahmadullah's footing is fine. The projections show that it would have hit middle. Impact: umpire's call, though, and Faf stays

commentary: Nasir Hossain to du Plessis, OUT Faf du Plessis steps out and holes out. Bangladesh have their man. Tossed up on middle, he skips down the track and mis-hits the lofted strike to the right of long-on. Sarkar runs across and takes it. Faf aimed to bisect deep midwicket and long-on. No dice. Big, big wicket for the hosts. South Africa five down...

commentary: Imran Tahir to Soumya Sarkar, SIX runs Bangladesh win, they square the series, and secure their Champions Trophy spot! Soumya seals it with a six. Tossed up and outside off, he goes for a slog-sweep. Rabada at deep midwicket leaps, gets both hands but can only parry it over the boundary, leaving the fans grooving and jiving. Mirpur in full blast...
